"n. 弹弓；弹射器 【英】 n.弹弓(slingshot);弹射器( hurling machine) n. (游戏用的, 或古代的发射大块石头或矛的军事器械)弹弓 = slingshot; (导弹、飞机的)弹射器 【例】The driver was catapulted through the windscreen 司机碰破挡风玻璃飞了出去. 【记】cata下, pult读: 炮塔. 炮塔可以用弹弓向下面发射石头－弹弓cata下, pult读: 炮他: 向下用炮打他－弹弓 【记】cata向下 + pull拉，向下拉弹弓 catapult (n.)  1570s, from Middle French catapulte and directly from Latin catapulta ""war machine for throwing,"" from Greek katapeltes, from kata ""against"" (see cata-) + base of pallein ""to toss, hurl"" (see pulse (n.1)). As an airplane-launching device on an aircraft-carrier by 1927. catapult (v.)  1848, ""to throw with a catapult,"" from catapult (n.). Intransitive sense by 1928. Related: Catapulted; catapulting."
